HEADWORD: Innermost
<hw>In"ner*most`</hw> <pr>(⟦icr⟧n"n⟦etil⟧r*m⟦omac⟧st`)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[A corruption of <ets>inmost</ets> due to influence
of <ets>inner</ets>. See <er>Inmost</er>.]</ety> <def>Farthest inward;
most remote from the outward part; inmost; deepest within.</def>
<rj><au>Prov. xviii. 8.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

